    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - 3300 Model - CAB FEATURES - Emergency exit controls - EXTENDED
        DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EXTENDED DESCRIPTION</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08298_X08298126H.xml" xrefid="f08298937">Emergency Exit Circuits</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <para>When an emergency exit is opened a circuit will close applying a ground signal to body builder connector
            (1007) pin 3. This will charge the emergency exit relay (1020). This will close a circuit between the zero
            volt reference signal and the system controller (1600) pin 25. When the ESC sees the zero volt signal, it
            will activate the emergency lights and buzzer.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
